
\Smesg\S:  Description

Syntax Summary:  mesg [n] [y]

Description:
     \Smesg\S stands for "message".  Use \Smesg\S to allow or prevent other
     users to write to your terminal.  \Smesg\S with the argument "n" prevents
     other users to write to your terminal. With the argument "y" \Smesg\S
     allows other users to write to your terminal.  \Smesg\S by itself prints
     the current permissions for your terminal.  See also:  write(1) for a
     command that might be used with \Smesg\S.
